<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="367" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[809,1421,1180,1447]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">
The 
<typeStatus box="[900,951,1180,1206]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">type</typeStatus>
specimen of this species was originally collected from an unspecified location in 
<collectingCountry box="[1336,1421,1214,1240]" name="Liberia" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Liberia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="FAHR, J." box="[817,966,1249,1275]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" pagination="497 - 499" refId="ref12785" refString="FAHR, J. 2013 e. Tadarida bemmeleni Gland-tailed free-tailed bat. Pp. 497 - 499, in The mammals of Africa. Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews and bats (M. HAPPOLD and D. C. D. HAPPOLD, eds.). Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Fahr, 2013 
<emphasis box="[953,966,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">e</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
). The occurrence of this species at Mt 
<collectingRegion box="[860,940,1283,1309]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Nimba</collectingRegion>
is mentioned only by 
<bibRefCitation author="FAHR, J." box="[1252,1415,1283,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" pagination="497 - 499" refId="ref12785" refString="FAHR, J. 2013 e. Tadarida bemmeleni Gland-tailed free-tailed bat. Pp. 497 - 499, in The mammals of Africa. Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews and bats (M. HAPPOLD and D. C. D. HAPPOLD, eds.). Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Fahr (2013 
<emphasis box="[1391,1404,1283,1309]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">e</emphasis>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who stated that it had been recorded in montane grassland at 
<quantity box="[958,1056,1352,1378]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" unit="m" value="1600.0">1,600 m</quantity>
(specimen in the Senckenberg Museum, Frankfurt). It was not recorded during this survey.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
